.TH GETMEM 2CCC
.SH NAME
getmem, getstk \- get a block of main memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B char *getmem(nbytes)
.br
.B int nbytes;
.sp
.B char *getstk(nbytes)
.br
.B int nbytes;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
In either form,
.I getmem
allocates a block of
.I nbytes
bytes of memory for the caller (using
.I malloc(3)
).  Note that malloc(3) and free(3) can be used directly by the user.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.I Getmem
returns the lowest word address in the allocated block;
.I getstk
returns the highest word address in the allocated block.
In either case, if
.I malloc
returns a null pointer, so will
.I getmem.
.SH SEE ALSO
freemem(2CCC), buffer(3CCC), malloc(3)
.SH BUGS
There is no way to protect memory, so the active stack may write into
regions returned by
either call.
